snippet.textDisplay:
Someone who is well-known on the Dublin cinema scene went on Twitter saying Stevie was mad for celebrating like he had won the League. He just showed his pathetic lack of insight. Celtic were always the benchmark against which Stevie's managerial progress was going to be measured and he started with a squad much weaker than the team which has totally dominated Scottish football in recent seasons. This win was the culmination of hundreds of hours of planning, coaching and managing from Stevie and his assistants.
For those of us who have followed his career since he was 18, it was never a question of if but when. There is still a long way to go with more work to be done, but this performance will only strengthen the belief of everyone at the club and add wind to their sails.
And tellingly, his celebration goes to prove that, if anything, he is even more obsessed as a manager than he was as a player and that is part of what makes him so special. Go on Stevie lad.
